PAST MEDICAL HISTORY
1.  Hyperlipidemia.  He has been on medication for several years.  His recent cholesterol panel from February 16th revealed a total cholesterol of 177, triglycerides of 80, HDL 48, and an LDL of 113.  He is on fish oil.
2.  Prior history of asthma. When he was a child he had severe asthma, but is no longer using an inhaler and he denies respiratory symptoms.
3.  Pericardial effusion, unclear etiology. In 2001 he developed a severe upper respiratory infection thought to be bronchitis and became quite short of breath.  His chest x-ray revealed a significant pericardial effusion.  He underwent minor surgery, a pericardial window it sounds like (I do not have these records), and the fluid was drained.  He had a follow-up echocardiogram which was normal. He was instructed should he ever develop a significant respiratory infection again that he should have a chest x-ray to make sure he does not have a recurrence. He does not remember the term endocarditis being used.
